This article is a Presidential Memorandum issued by President Barack Obama in 2010 regarding the implementation of the National HIV/AIDS Strategy. The memorandum emphasizes the need for new actions to prevent HIV infection and better serve people living with HIV. It states that the Federal Government must work in new ways across agency lines and in partnerships with State, tribal, and local governments. The memorandum designates lead agencies responsible for implementing the Strategy and requires them to submit operational plans for implementation. The Secretary of Health and Human Services is tasked with improving coordination of domestic HIV/AIDS programs and activities, both within the department and with other agencies. The memorandum also outlines responsibilities for other agencies, including the Department of Defense, Department of State, and Equal Employment Opportunity Commission. It concludes with general provisions and the authorization for publication in the Federal Register.